  "articleSummary": "The article argues that \"generative UI\" is not a single technology but a multi-layered concept, and the biggest mistake is treating it as one choice. It presents a four-layer model (product shell, UI composition model, runtime/transport, agent/tool backend) to clarify the ecosystem, using examples like AG-UI, A2UI, and CopilotKit to show how different tools operate at different layers. The piece also introduces a control spectrum balancing developer control and agent freedom, from tool-to-component rendering to open-ended generated HTML. Aimed at developers and architects building LLM applications, the tone is analytical and taxonomic, with recurring metaphors of \"layers\" and \"training wheels\" for chat-based interfaces.",
